lg.l:
And rays refract from the oldworld
                    heaven of
                    time;

Began
                    the music of the heaven
                    of dawn;

And
                    earth-born lightnings
                    out of bloodbright spray;

And had
                    for scroll the night,
                    for scribe the day!

Exalted over
                    twilight and her
                    star;

Since
                    earth bore ever
                    women that were fair;

Of
                    seas less monstrous
                    than the births they bred;

Shakespeare, a
                    heaven of heavenly eyes
                    beholden;
